        "meta_description": "Earlier this week, scriptwriter Jyoti Kapoor won a landmark case of copyright violation and breach of confidence against Bollywood director Kunal Kohli after eight months of legal tussle. The Supreme Court ordered Kunal Kohli to pay Kapoor Rs 25 lakh as compensation and give her credit for 'story/idea'. Juhi Chaturvedi, scriptwriter of Bollywood hits such as Vicky Donor and Piku, speaks to Ritika Bhatia on what the judgment bodes for writers' creative rights in a film industry ruled by producers and superstars.",
